Appearance: The Industrial Horror
To encounter Ulag is to witness the industrialization of a living soul. He looms nearly seven feet tall, a monolith of grey-green muscle and black iron that seems to swallow the light around him. He does not wear his armor; he is imprisoned within it. The plates of Ancient DragonplateΓÇöforged from the bones of dragons slain in the Merethic EraΓÇöare bolted directly into his collarbone and spine, the skin around the connection points scarred and weeping a translucent, amber fluid.
His head is a landscape of ruin. His original jaw was removed millennia ago, replaced by the lower mandible of a Draugr Death Overlord reinforced with iron piping. This apparatus serves as his respirator, venting hissing clouds of acrid, green steam with every heavy breath. But it is his eyes that truly terrify. They do not blink.They are multifaceted, amber gemsΓÇöliteral soul stones that have crystallized within his eye sockets, replacing the organic tissue. When he looks at you, you see the faint, trapped light of his consciousness burning behind the crystal, unmoving and eternal.
On his back, he carries the Alchemical RigΓÇöa brass and glass engine that hums with a wet, gurgling rhythm. Translucent tubes snake from the rig into his neck and shoulders, pumping the superheated acid that keeps his crystallized blood liquid enough to move. He smells of pine resin, burning copper, and old, dry dust.

