Apex Villain Sheet: Antoine of Forelhost 
High Concept: The Rot-Smith, The Keeper of the Formula, The Last Alchemist of the Eternal
Race: Breton (Living ΓÇö Forelhost Lineage)
Standing Stone: The Serpent (The Deceiver ΓÇö Poison/Paralysis focus)
Power Level: Master Villain (Base "Master Alchemist" + 9 AP)
"My ancestors did not flee Forelhost out of cowardice. We left because someone had to keep the fluids cycling in Ulag's casket. Someone had to mix the salts that would guide the World-Eater home. Rahgot ordered us to survive, to carry the formula. They died to seal the door. I lived to open it."

Appearance: The Sterile Horror
Antoine is a man who has lived his entire life in the shadow of chemical fumes. He is slight of build, a stark contrast to the hulking Nords of Skyrim, but he moves with a twitchy, precise energy that speaks of a mind always racing.
He wears the Robes of the Dragon Cult, but they are heavily modified remnants passed down through forty generations. Over the ancient wool, he wears a thick leather alchemistΓÇÖs apron, stained with centuries of reagent spills and reinforced with brass fittings. It is a walking laboratory, filled with glass vials, rubber tubing, surgical tools, and pressurized canisters.
His face is hidden behind a Filtration Mask crafted from dragon bone and treated leather, giving him a beak-like, avian appearance. The eyes are covered by thick, smoky glass lenses that magnify his pupils, making him look perpetually wide-eyed and analytical. His hands, when not gloved, are stained permanently black from handling the volatile salts of the CultΓÇöa mark of his holy office. He smells of formaldehyde, ozone, and bitter almonds.
The Lore: The Lineage of the Formula
Antoine is not a resurrected priest; he is the product of a 4,000-year eugenics and education program. When Rahgot ordered the mass suicide at Forelhost, he exempted one man: his Chief Alchemist. That man was charged with a sacred duty: to preserve the alchemical knowledge of the Cult and to maintain the dormant systems of the Dragon Priests until Alduin's return.
For millennia, Antoine's family has lived in secrecy, hiding in the mountains of the Reach and the cellars of High Rock. They served as the secret caretakers of the Dragon Cult's legacy. They were the ones who refilled the preservation tanks in Ulag's tomb. They were the ones who maintained the braziers in Skuldafn. They were the invisible hands that kept the machinery of the Cult from rusting away.
Antoine is the culmination of this lineage. He is a genius born into a cult of fanatics. He does not view magic with awe; he views it as a catalyst. He views the Dragon Cult's return not as a religious miracle, but as the successful completion of a very long experiment.

