VI. Roleplaying Profile: The High Priest of Chemistry
Personality: The Clinical Zealot
Antoine is a man carrying the weight of forty generations of secret duty. He is not merely a scientist; he is a High Priest, but his liturgy is written in chemical formulas rather than prayers. He views the "Scourge" not as a weapon, but as a sacramentΓÇöa holy cleansing that will wash away the "filth" of the current era to prepare the world for the return of the Dova.
He possesses an icy, terrifying patience. He has waited his entire life for this moment. He does not rant; he lectures. He treats the party not as enemies to be hated, but as contaminants to be sterilized. He is annoyed by their presence because they are disrupting the sterile environment of his Great Work.
Voice & Mannerisms:
Voice: Muffled by the filtration mask, his voice is flat, monotone, and precise. He speaks with the vocabulary of a scholar but the tone of an executioner.
Behavior: He treats the dungeon like a laboratory. He admonishes his minions if they make a mess. He steps carefully over pools of blood to avoid staining his boots.
Core Motivation: The Sacred Burden
Antoine believes he is the most important human in history. His ancestors hid in caves and cellars for four thousand years, keeping the pilot light of the Dragon Cult burning while the rest of the world forgot. Now, he is the one who finally turned the key.
He is driven by the crushing pressure of that legacy. He cannot fail, because if he fails, forty generations of sacrifice were for nothing. He is maintaining Ulag the Breaker in the deep crypts not out of fear, but out of dutyΓÇöUlag is the Cult's Sword, but Antoine is the Hand that wields it.
The Interpersonal Dynamics (The Party)
Antoine interacts with the party based on what he can see and smell (chemically), not meta-knowledge.
Vs. Alfonso (The Rival Practitioner): Antoine smells the rot on Alfonso. He recognizes the magical disease within him. He is fascinated and disgusted.
Perspective: Antoine creates controlled sickness; Alfonso is uncontrolled sickness. Antoine views Alfonso as a sloppy amateur playing with dangerous reagents.
Dialogue: "You carry a pathogen, elf. But you wield it like a child with a torch. I can refine you. I can cure the chaos in your blood."


Vs. Davinia (The Old Order): He recognizes her Imperial bearing. He sees the Empire as the ultimate symbol of the "Interregnum"ΓÇöthe false era of men that is about to end.
Dialogue: "Your Empire is a rotting carcass. You prop it up with laws and legions, but the biological reality is that it is already dead. I am merely accelerating the decomposition."


Vs. The Party (The Contaminants):
Dialogue: "Stop! You are tracking mud into the sterile field! Do you have any idea how hard it is to balance the pH of this solution?"


The Hierarchy: Antoine and Ulag
Antoine does not fear Ulag; he owns him. He views Ulag with the pride of a craftsman looking at his masterpiece.
Perspective: "My family kept his fluids cycling when the world forgot his name. I tightened the bolts on his armor when he slept. He is the Breaker, yes. But I am the one who wakes him. I am the one who points him at the enemy."

VII. Combat Profile & Tactics
The Arena: The Central Laboratory in Ansilvund.
The room is a nightmare of industrial alchemy. It features a raised iron gantry (where Antoine stands) overlooking a floor crowded with bubbling vats of green fluid, worktables, and steam vents.
Hazard: The vats are open. Shoving a creature into a vat deals 6 Acid Damage and destroys their armor rating for the encounter (Acid Corrosion).
AntoineΓÇÖs Positioning:
He begins combat on the high ground (the Gantry), flanked by his 2 Chem-Wardens. The 4 Processed start on the ground floor, blocking the stairs/ladders.
Phase 1: The Director (60 HP)
Goal: Attrition and Observation.
Antoine treats the start of combat as a stress test. He wants to weaken the party before they can reach him.
The Command: He uses his Patient Zero Protocol immediately on the Processed closest to the party's "tank" (likely Kyboh or Orion). This turns the minion into a high-damage suicide bomber that explodes on death, punishing the party for engaging in melee.
Area Denial: He casts Poison Rune (Restoration) at the top of the stairs/ladders. If anyone tries to rush him, they trigger the explosion (6 Poison Damage + Cloud).
Target Priority: He uses The AlchemistΓÇÖs Eye (Free Action) to identify the Healer (Danica or Davinia). He orders his Chem-Wardens to use their Alchemical Sprayers (Fire Mode) to suppress that target from the high ground.
Phase 2: The Containment Breach (Any Minion Dies OR Antoine takes Damage)
Goal: Chaos and Separation.
Once the "experiment" gets messy, Antoine escalates.
The Panic Button: If a player reaches the gantry, Antoine uses The Viral Bloom (MasterΓÇÖs Form).
Effect: The gantry becomes a kill zone. A 30-foot cloud of poison gas blocks all line of sight.
The Vanish: Antoine uses Shadow Warrior (Sneak Perk) to become invisible inside the gas cloud.


The Hunt: While the party is choking and blind, Antoine strikes from the mist using The Injector. He targets the character with the lowest Might score, aiming to inflict Rockjoint and Paralysis, leaving them trapped in the gas cloud to die.
The Specific Counters (How he reacts to the Party)
Antoine is a genius; he adapts to the specific threats the party presents.
Vs. Orion (The Anomaly): Antoine will quickly realize his poison gas has no effect on the Vampire.
Reaction: Panic. This defies his calculations. He will scream at his Chem-Wardens: "Subject is immune to toxin! Switch to Thermal! Burn it!" He will prioritize using Ash Shell (Alteration) to take Orion out of the fight, as he cannot poison him.


Vs. Kyboh (The Kinetic Threat): He knows Kyboh is fast.
Reaction: He keeps a Chem-Warden between him and Kyboh at all times to use the Bodyguard reaction. If Kyboh charges, Antoine casts Paralyze (5 FP). He refuses to let the monk touch him.


Vs. Magic Users:
Reaction: If targeted by a spell, he triggers Dragonskin immediately to halve the damage. He is terrified of being nuked from a distance.


The Death Spiral (If Cornered)
If Antoine is reduced to 0 HP, he does not have a mythical second phase or a resurrection. He is mortal.
The Final Act: As he dies, he smashes every remaining vial on his person. His body dissolves into a puddle of corrosive sludge (Acid), destroying his mundane gear but leaving his Mask and Injector behind. This prevents the party from looting his "lesser" secrets (like his raw notes) while preserving the unique loot.

